Install the neccessary libaries. leaps is used to install the regsubset functions to perform a subset regression analysis.

library(car)
library(leaps)

We then read the csv file which is from this link:https://www.kaggle.com/ronitf/heart-disease-uci.

df = read.csv('heart.csv')
View(df)

Initialise the independent variables.

age = as.numeric(df$age)
sex = as.numeric(df$sex)
cp = as.numeric(df$cp)
trtbps = as.numeric(df$trtbps)
chol = as.numeric(df$chol)
fbs = as.numeric(df$fbs)
restecg = as.numeric(df$restecg)
exng = as.numeric(df$exng)
oldpeak = as.numeric(df$oldpeak)
slp = as.numeric(df$slp)
caa = as.numeric(df$caa)
thall = as.numeric(df$thall)
output = as.numeric(df$output)

Initialise the dependent variable.

We transform the dependent variable to make the variable normally distributed.

This is to satisfy the assumptions made regarding linear regression.

thalachh = as.numeric(df$thalachh)
hist(thalachh)
thalachh = (as.numeric(df$thalachh))^(1.6031)
hist(thalachh)

We plot the dependent variables against the independent variables.

We can see the summary of the regression model.

These are the main points that could be derived.

The Multiple R squared is 0.3986.

The Adjusted R squared is 0.3737.

The overall regression is significant.

The sample standard deviation is 580.4.

The intercept,age,trtbps,exng,slp and output are statistically significant. The rest of the variables are not.

model = lm(thalachh~age+sex+trtbps+chol+fbs+restecg+exng+oldpeak+slp+caa+thall+output)
summary(model)

Here we apply subset regression on to the model.

We extract the model with the highest adjusted R squared which is thalachh ~ age + trtbps + chol + exng + slp + thall + output.

We extract the model with the lowest mallow statistic which is thalachh ~ age + trtbps + chol + exng + slp + output.

We extract the model with the lowest Bayesian information criterion which is thalachh ~ age + trtbps + exng + slp + output.

subset = regsubsets(thalachh~age+sex+trtbps+chol+fbs+restecg+exng+oldpeak+slp+caa+thall+output,data=df,nvmax=ncol(df)-1)
summarysubsets = summary(subset)

The best model is thalachh ~ age + trtbps + chol + exng + slp + output.

So we select all the models that were selected by stepwise and subset regression and create new models.

newmodel = lm(thalachh ~ age + trtbps + chol + exng + slp + output)
newmodel1 = lm(thalachh ~ output + age + slp + exng + trtbps + chol)
newmodel2 = lm(thalachh ~ age + trtbps + chol + exng + slp + thall + output)
newmodel5 = lm(thalachh ~ age + trtbps + exng + slp + output)

Main points from the summary of the thalachh ~ age + trtbps + chol + exng + slp + output model.

1.(10% level) All the variables are statistically significant

2.Trtbps and chol are not statistically significant based on anova table.

2.Overall regression is significant.

3.The sample standard deviation 578.3.

4.Multiple R squared is 0.3907.

5.Adjusted R squared is 0.3784.

Regarding the unusual values and influential observations of the model.

  1. Number of high leverage values are 8.

  2. Number of very high leverage values are 2.

  3. There are no influential observations in the data.

Regarding regression assumptions:

1.Linearity assumption is valid based on residual plots

2.Constant variance assumption is valid based on residual plots

3.Normality assumption is not valid based on qqplot and shapiro-wilk test.

4.There is no perfect multicollinearity based on variance inflation factor.
